# tag-name-per-line allowlist for `scripts/audit-knowledge-stores.py --strict`.
#
# Each entry names a `data/<tag>/knowledge.db` whose pre-patch
# sanitiser escapes are knowledge of record and must NOT block CI.
# Any *new* tag added to `data/` that has escapes will fail the gate.
#
# Format: one tag name per line; lines starting with `#` are comments.
#
# Public-release default: empty. The `data/` tree is gitignored so
# no historical pre-patch escapes ship with the repo. If you run a
# fresh sweep against a model whose output the current sanitiser
# does not yet cover, document the case in the corresponding
# MODEL-SWEEP-REPORT-vN.md entry, add the tag here, and open a PR
# extending the sanitiser to cover the new code points.
